{"questionId":"29942255","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A survey at a swimming pool is given to one adult in each family. The age of the&nbsp;adult, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> years old, and of their eldest child, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> years old, are recorded.</p>\n<p>The ages of the eldest child are summarized in the following box and whisker diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f1b12086f78c59245f2e522bf19532385a544318.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the largest value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> that would not be considered an outlier.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>IQR</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mtext>IQR</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29942255","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.3a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the largest value of c that would not be considered an outlier.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability